{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":556,"text":"Our emotions influence\nevery aspect of our lives,"},{"time":4573,"text":"from our health and how we learn,\nto how we do business and make decisions,"},{"time":8149,"text":"big ones and small."},{"time":10672,"text":"Our emotions also influence\nhow we connect with one another."},{"time":15132,"text":"We've evolved to live\nin a world like this,"},{"time":19108,"text":"but instead, we're living\nmore and more of our lives like this --"},{"time":23427,"text":"this is the text message\nfrom my daughter last night --"},{"time":26561,"text":"in a world that's devoid of emotion."},{"time":29301,"text":"So I'm on a mission to change that."},{"time":31252,"text":"I want to bring emotions\nback into our digital experiences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36223,"text":"I started on this path 15 years ago."},{"time":39300,"text":"I was a computer scientist in Egypt,"},{"time":41366,"text":"and I had just gotten accepted to\na Ph.D. program at Cambridge University."},{"time":45871,"text":"So I did something quite unusual"},{"time":47984,"text":"for a young newlywed Muslim Egyptian wife:"},{"time":53599,"text":"With the support of my husband,\nwho had to stay in Egypt,"},{"time":56598,"text":"I packed my bags and I moved to England."},{"time":59616,"text":"At Cambridge, thousands of miles\naway from home,"},{"time":62844,"text":"I realized I was spending\nmore hours with my laptop"},{"time":66257,"text":"than I did with any other human."},{"time":68486,"text":"Yet despite this intimacy, my laptop\nhad absolutely no idea how I was feeling."},{"time":73339,"text":"It had no idea if I was happy,"},{"time":76550,"text":"having a bad day, or stressed, confused,"},{"time":79538,"text":"and so that got frustrating."},{"time":83600,"text":"Even worse, as I communicated\nonline with my family back home,"},{"time":89421,"text":"I felt that all my emotions\ndisappeared in cyberspace."},{"time":92703,"text":"I was homesick, I was lonely,\nand on some days I was actually crying,"},{"time":97858,"text":"but all I had to communicate\nthese emotions was this."},{"time":102786,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":104806,"text":"Today's technology\nhas lots of I.Q., but no E.Q.;"},{"time":109780,"text":"lots of cognitive intelligence,\nbut no emotional intelligence."},{"time":112956,"text":"So that got me thinking,"},{"time":115153,"text":"what if our technology\ncould sense our emotions?"},{"time":118777,"text":"What if our devices could sense\nhow we felt and reacted accordingly,"},{"time":122853,"text":"just the way an emotionally\nintelligent friend would?"},{"time":126666,"text":"Those questions led me and my team"},{"time":130230,"text":"to create technologies that can read\nand respond to our emotions,"},{"time":134607,"text":"and our starting point was the human face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138577,"text":"So our human face happens to be\none of the most powerful channels"},{"time":141750,"text":"that we all use to communicate\nsocial and emotional states,"},{"time":145766,"text":"everything from enjoyment, surprise,"},{"time":148776,"text":"empathy and curiosity."},{"time":152979,"text":"In emotion science, we call each\nfacial muscle movement an action unit."},{"time":157907,"text":"So for example, action unit 12,"},{"time":160832,"text":"it's not a Hollywood blockbuster,"},{"time":162870,"text":"it is actually a lip corner pull,\nwhich is the main component of a smile."},{"time":166312,"text":"Try it everybody. Let's get\nsome smiles going on."},{"time":169300,"text":"Another example is action unit 4.\nIt's the brow furrow."},{"time":171954,"text":"It's when you draw your eyebrows together"},{"time":174192,"text":"and you create all\nthese textures and wrinkles."},{"time":176459,"text":"We don't like them, but it's\na strong indicator of a negative emotion."},{"time":180754,"text":"So we have about 45 of these action units,"},{"time":182960,"text":"and they combine to express\nhundreds of emotions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186350,"text":"Teaching a computer to read\nthese facial emotions is hard,"},{"time":190251,"text":"because these action units,\nthey can be fast, they're subtle,"},{"time":193223,"text":"and they combine in many different ways."},{"time":195777,"text":"So take, for example,\nthe smile and the smirk."},{"time":199515,"text":"They look somewhat similar,\nbut they mean very different things."},{"time":203268,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":204986,"text":"So the smile is positive,"},{"time":207990,"text":"a smirk is often negative."},{"time":209260,"text":"Sometimes a smirk\ncan make you become famous."},{"time":213136,"text":"But seriously, it's important\nfor a computer to be able"},{"time":215960,"text":"to tell the difference\nbetween the two expressions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218815,"text":"So how do we do that?"},{"time":220627,"text":"We give our algorithms"},{"time":222414,"text":"tens of thousands of examples\nof people we know to be smiling,"},{"time":226524,"text":"from different ethnicities, ages, genders,"},{"time":229589,"text":"and we do the same for smirks."},{"time":232400,"text":"And then, using deep learning,"},{"time":233954,"text":"the algorithm looks for all these\ntextures and wrinkles"},{"time":236810,"text":"and shape changes on our face,"},{"time":239390,"text":"and basically learns that all smiles\nhave common characteristics,"},{"time":242592,"text":"all smirks have subtly\ndifferent characteristics."},{"time":245773,"text":"And the next time it sees a new face,"},{"time":248141,"text":"it essentially learns that"},{"time":250440,"text":"this face has the same\ncharacteristics of a smile,"},{"time":253473,"text":"and it says, \"Aha, I recognize this.\nThis is a smile expression.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":258381,"text":"So the best way to demonstrate\nhow this technology works"},{"time":261181,"text":"is to try a live demo,"},{"time":263317,"text":"so I need a volunteer,\npreferably somebody with a face."},{"time":267230,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":269564,"text":"Cloe's going to be our volunteer today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273325,"text":"So over the past five years, we've moved\nfrom being a research project at MIT"},{"time":277783,"text":"to a company,"},{"time":278939,"text":"where my team has worked really hard\nto make this technology work,"},{"time":282131,"text":"as we like to say, in the wild."},{"time":284540,"text":"And we've also shrunk it so that\nthe core emotion engine"},{"time":287210,"text":"works on any mobile device\nwith a camera, like this iPad."},{"time":290530,"text":"So let's give this a try."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294756,"text":"As you can see, the algorithm\nhas essentially found Cloe's face,"},{"time":298680,"text":"so it's this white bounding box,"},{"time":300372,"text":"and it's tracking the main\nfeature points on her face,"},{"time":302943,"text":"so her eyebrows, her eyes,\nher mouth and her nose."},{"time":305799,"text":"The question is,\ncan it recognize her expression?"},{"time":308786,"text":"So we're going to test the machine."},{"time":310457,"text":"So first of all, give me your poker face.\nYep, awesome. (Laughter)"},{"time":314643,"text":"And then as she smiles,\nthis is a genuine smile, it's great."},{"time":317456,"text":"So you can see the green bar\ngo up as she smiles."},{"time":319756,"text":"Now that was a big smile."},{"time":320978,"text":"Can you try a subtle smile\nto see if the computer can recognize?"},{"time":324021,"text":"It does recognize subtle smiles as well."},{"time":326352,"text":"We've worked really hard\nto make that happen."},{"time":328477,"text":"And then eyebrow raised,\nindicator of surprise."},{"time":331439,"text":"Brow furrow, which is\nan indicator of confusion."},{"time":335688,"text":"Frown. Yes, perfect."},{"time":339695,"text":"So these are all the different\naction units. There's many more of them."},{"time":343188,"text":"This is just a slimmed-down demo."},{"time":345220,"text":"But we call each reading\nan emotion data point,"},{"time":348368,"text":"and then they can fire together\nto portray different emotions."},{"time":351337,"text":"So on the right side of the demo --\nlook like you're happy."},{"time":355990,"text":"So that's joy. Joy fires up."},{"time":357444,"text":"And then give me a disgust face."},{"time":359371,"text":"Try to remember what it was like\nwhen Zayn left One Direction."},{"time":363643,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":365153,"text":"Yeah, wrinkle your nose. Awesome."},{"time":369495,"text":"And the valence is actually quite\nnegative, so you must have been a big fan."},{"time":373226,"text":"So valence is how positive\nor negative an experience is,"},{"time":375926,"text":"and engagement is how\nexpressive she is as well."},{"time":378712,"text":"So imagine if Cloe had access\nto this real-time emotion stream,"},{"time":382126,"text":"and she could share it\nwith anybody she wanted to."},{"time":384935,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":387858,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":393749,"text":"So, so far, we have amassed\n12 billion of these emotion data points."},{"time":399019,"text":"It's the largest emotion\ndatabase in the world."},{"time":401630,"text":"We've collected it\nfrom 2.9 million face videos,"},{"time":404593,"text":"people who have agreed\nto share their emotions with us,"},{"time":407193,"text":"and from 75 countries around the world."},{"time":410398,"text":"It's growing every day."},{"time":412603,"text":"It blows my mind away"},{"time":414670,"text":"that we can now quantify something\nas personal as our emotions,"},{"time":417865,"text":"and we can do it at this scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420100,"text":"So what have we learned to date?"},{"time":423057,"text":"Gender."},{"time":425388,"text":"Our data confirms something\nthat you might suspect."},{"time":429034,"text":"Women are more expressive than men."},{"time":430891,"text":"Not only do they smile more,\ntheir smiles last longer,"},{"time":433574,"text":"and we can now really quantify\nwhat it is that men and women"},{"time":436478,"text":"respond to differently."},{"time":438614,"text":"Let's do culture: So in the United States,"},{"time":440904,"text":"women are 40 percent\nmore expressive than men,"},{"time":444108,"text":"but curiously, we don't see any difference\nin the U.K. between men and women."},{"time":447753,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":451296,"text":"Age: People who are 50 years and older"},{"time":455323,"text":"are 25 percent more emotive\nthan younger people."},{"time":459899,"text":"Women in their 20s smile a lot more\nthan men the same age,"},{"time":463751,"text":"perhaps a necessity for dating."},{"time":467590,"text":"But perhaps what surprised us\nthe most about this data"},{"time":470207,"text":"is that we happen\nto be expressive all the time,"},{"time":473410,"text":"even when we are sitting\nin front of our devices alone,"},{"time":476243,"text":"and it's not just when we're watching\ncat videos on Facebook."},{"time":480217,"text":"We are expressive when we're emailing,\ntexting, shopping online,"},{"time":483227,"text":"or even doing our taxes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485527,"text":"Where is this data used today?"},{"time":487919,"text":"In understanding how we engage with media,"},{"time":490682,"text":"so understanding virality\nand voting behavior;"},{"time":493166,"text":"and also empowering\nor emotion-enabling technology,"},{"time":495906,"text":"and I want to share some examples\nthat are especially close to my heart."},{"time":501197,"text":"Emotion-enabled wearable glasses\ncan help individuals"},{"time":504265,"text":"who are visually impaired\nread the faces of others,"},{"time":507493,"text":"and it can help individuals\non the autism spectrum interpret emotion,"},{"time":511680,"text":"something that they really struggle with."},{"time":515918,"text":"In education, imagine\nif your learning apps"},{"time":518777,"text":"sense that you're confused and slow down,"},{"time":521587,"text":"or that you're bored, so it's sped up,"},{"time":523444,"text":"just like a great teacher\nwould in a classroom."},{"time":527043,"text":"What if your wristwatch tracked your mood,"},{"time":529644,"text":"or your car sensed that you're tired,"},{"time":532337,"text":"or perhaps your fridge\nknows that you're stressed,"},{"time":534885,"text":"so it auto-locks to prevent you\nfrom binge eating. (Laughter)"},{"time":540951,"text":"I would like that, yeah."},{"time":543668,"text":"What if, when I was in Cambridge,"},{"time":545595,"text":"I had access to my real-time\nemotion stream,"},{"time":547908,"text":"and I could share that with my family\nback home in a very natural way,"},{"time":551437,"text":"just like I would've if we were all\nin the same room together?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":555408,"text":"I think five years down the line,"},{"time":558550,"text":"all our devices are going\nto have an emotion chip,"},{"time":560887,"text":"and we won't remember what it was like\nwhen we couldn't just frown at our device"},{"time":564951,"text":"and our device would say, \"Hmm,\nyou didn't like that, did you?\""},{"time":569200,"text":"Our biggest challenge is that there are\nso many applications of this technology,"},{"time":572961,"text":"my team and I realize that we can't\nbuild them all ourselves,"},{"time":575864,"text":"so we've made this technology available\nso that other developers"},{"time":579360,"text":"can get building and get creative."},{"time":581474,"text":"We recognize that\nthere are potential risks"},{"time":585560,"text":"and potential for abuse,"},{"time":587627,"text":"but personally, having spent\nmany years doing this,"},{"time":590576,"text":"I believe that the benefits to humanity"},{"time":593548,"text":"from having emotionally\nintelligent technology"},{"time":595823,"text":"far outweigh the potential for misuse."},{"time":599399,"text":"And I invite you all to be\npart of the conversation."},{"time":601930,"text":"The more people who know\nabout this technology,"},{"time":604484,"text":"the more we can all have a voice\nin how it's being used."},{"time":609081,"text":"So as more and more\nof our lives become digital,"},{"time":613655,"text":"we are fighting a losing battle\ntrying to curb our usage of devices"},{"time":617153,"text":"in order to reclaim our emotions."},{"time":620622,"text":"So what I'm trying to do instead\nis to bring emotions into our technology"},{"time":624536,"text":"and make our technologies more responsive."},{"time":626765,"text":"So I want those devices\nthat have separated us"},{"time":629435,"text":"to bring us back together."},{"time":631897,"text":"And by humanizing technology,\nwe have this golden opportunity"},{"time":636485,"text":"to reimagine how we\nconnect with machines,"},{"time":639782,"text":"and therefore, how we, as human beings,"},{"time":644263,"text":"connect with one another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646167,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648327,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}